<TITLE> AL, JP reach candidacy deal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 8 (bdnews24.com)  The Awami League and its electoral ally Jatiya Party have reached a deal on parliamentary polls candidates, allaying fears over the issue, the AL spokesperson said on Monday. "We have finalised seat distribution with Jatiya Party. Awami League is fully ready for elections," Syed Ashraful Islam, also joint general secretary, said to reporters at Sudha Sadan, the AL president's home at Dhanmondi. Ashraful said his party prioritised cutting the prices of commodities in its election manifesto. "The prices of commodities must be brought within people's reach," he said. "The election is a must to create new employment. Our main target will be to raise production and reduce inflation." "We have to create an environment conduce to investment. We have to bring investment in the country, local or foreign. There is no alternative to it," the AL spokesman said. He reiterated the demand for lifting the state of emergency immediately, he said: "We will not be able to go to people if emergency rule is not lifted." Ashraful did not believe the shortage of time would be a problem in election campaigning. "We have to launch election campaign considering the limitations. We will maintain contact with people through short message service, internet and video conference," he said. bd
